# VOLT Display Manager — udev rules for display hotplug
#
# These rules trigger awareness of display changes through DRM events.
#
# IMPORTANT:
#   Do NOT run xrandr directly from udev. Udev events fire in an
#   environment without DISPLAY, XAUTHORITY, or user session context.
#
#   Instead, these rules notify the volt-display-hotplug systemd user
#   service, which runs inside the graphical session and has full
#   X11 access.
#
# Strategy:
#   Tag the event for systemd user instance awareness.
#   The hotplug watcher polls xrandr independently; these rules
#   serve as supplementary triggers for faster reaction.

ACTION=="change", SUBSYSTEM=="drm", KERNEL=="card*", \
  TAG+="systemd", \
  ENV{SYSTEMD_USER_WANTS}="volt-display-hotplug.service"

# Also react to hotplug of specific connectors (HDMI/DP)
ACTION=="change", SUBSYSTEM=="drm", KERNEL=="card*-HDMI-*", \
  TAG+="systemd"

ACTION=="change", SUBSYSTEM=="drm", KERNEL=="card*-DP-*", \
  TAG+="systemd"

# Known limitations:
#   - udev may fire before the connector state is fully settled.
#     The VDM debouncer (500ms) mitigates this.
#   - Some GPU drivers do not emit connector-level udev events.
#     In that case, the hotplug service's 2-second poll loop
#     serves as the reliable fallback.
